The subject gives the basic knowledge about TMJ diseases, salivary gland diseases, precancerous, benign  tumour and tumour like lesions. Clinical features, diagnosis and treatment of these diseases is discussed.Students learn to diagnose these diseases. Practical work is performed at the outpatient Dental Clinic and in the Department of Maxillo-facial Surgery. Students learn methods of conservative treatment, preparing splints in case of maxillofacial fractures, principles of the treatment of soft tissue injuries of the maxillofacial region and surgical treatment of the benign tumours and tumor-like lesions. The clinical work performed by the student has been analyzed with the tutor, the student has received feedback and the work has been included in the student's e-portfolio.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of the subject is to give the basic knowledge of injuries in the maxillo-facial region, tumourlike lesions and benign tumours,  salivary gland and TMJ diseases and about teeth implantation. Clinical features, diagnosis and treatment of these diseases are discussed.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  1. Knows theoretically etiology and symptomatology  in the maxillo-facial region diseases. 2. Is able to diagnose diseases using contemporary diagnostic methods and be able to compose the treatment plan. 3. Is able to perform intraoral operations: remove teeth and teeth roots, is able to perform atypical tooth removal and incisions on oral mucosa. 4. Student has an overview about  diagnose and treatment of the patients in the department of Maxillo-Facial Surgery.
